[2]
Date: 4 Jul 2007
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

Zika, Dengue and Chikungunya share many epidemiological, clinical and
geographic features. (See maps at
http://exhibit.gideononline.com/zika.jpg). An etiological diagnosis
for febrile rash in these regions will increasingly depend upon viral
studies.
--
Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
